  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best iOS calendar app that allows you to cross off EVENTS as you go through the day?",
  "response": "When it comes to selecting the best iOS calendar app that allows you to **cross off or mark events as completed** throughout your day, several top-tier options stand out. These apps not only offer robust calendar functionalities but also integrate task management features that make tracking and completing your daily events seamless. Here are some of the best choices:\n\n### 1. **Fantastical**\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Intuitive Interface:** Fantastical boasts a user-friendly design with natural language event creation, making it easy to add events quickly.\n- **Task Integration:** Integrates with task managers like Todoist, Wunderlist, and Apple Reminders, allowing you to manage tasks alongside your calendar events.\n- **Marking Events as Done:** While primarily a calendar app, Fantastical allows you to categorize events and tasks, making it easier to visually distinguish and mark completed items.\n- **Widgets and Notifications:** Offers customizable widgets and smart notifications to keep you updated throughout the day.\n\n**Why It\u2019s Great for Crossing Off Events:**\nFantastical\u2019s integration with task management systems lets you treat events similarly to tasks, providing checkboxes or marking options to cross off events as you complete them.\n\n### 2. **BusyCal**\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Customizable Views:** Offers various calendar views (day, week, month, year) with customizable display options.\n- **Action Schemes:** You can create custom shortcuts to perform actions like marking an event as done, adding notes, or moving events.\n- **Smart Filters and To-Dos:** Integrates to-dos with calendar events, allowing you to check off completed tasks directly from the calendar interface.\n- **Sync Options:** Seamlessly syncs with iCloud, Google, Exchange, and other calendar services.\n\n**Why It\u2019s Great for Crossing Off Events:**\nBusyCal\u2019s action schemes and to-do integration make it straightforward to mark events as completed. You can customize actions to include visual indicators that help you easily cross off events as your day progresses.\n\n### 3. **Microsoft Outlook**\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Unified Inbox and Calendar:** Combines email, calendar, and contacts in one app for streamlined management.\n- **Task Integration with Microsoft To Do:** Integrates seamlessly with Microsoft To Do, allowing you to manage and mark tasks and events as completed.\n- **Focused Inbox:** Helps prioritize important emails, indirectly aiding in managing your schedule more efficiently.\n- **Customizable Notifications:** Offers robust notification settings to keep you informed about upcoming events and deadlines.\n\n**Why It\u2019s Great for Crossing Off Events:**\nWith its integration with Microsoft To Do, you can effectively manage and mark events as completed within Outlook, benefiting from a unified workspace for both communication and scheduling.\n\n### 4. **TickTick**\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Calendar and Task Management:** Combines a powerful task manager with a versatile calendar view.\n- **Checklists and Reminders:** Allows you to create checklists for events and set reminders to ensure you complete them.\n- **Habit Tracking:** Offers habit tracking features to encourage consistency in your daily routines.\n- **Widgets and Integrations:** Provides customizable widgets and integrates with various other apps and services.\n\n**Why It\u2019s Great for Crossing Off Events:**\nTickTick\u2019s combination of calendar and task management lets you assign tasks to calendar events and easily check them off as you complete each one, providing a clear visual representation of your daily progress.\n\n### 5. **Apple Calendar with Third-Party Integrations**\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Seamless Integration:** Natively integrates with iOS, macOS, and other Apple services.\n- **Siri Support:** Allows voice commands to add and manage events.\n- **Third-Party App Support:** Can be enhanced with third-party apps and widgets to add functionalities like marking events as completed.\n\n**Why It\u2019s Great for Crossing Off Events:**\nWhile Apple Calendar itself doesn\u2019t natively support crossing off events, combining it with task management apps like Apple Reminders or third-party tools can provide the desired functionality.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nChoosing the best calendar app depends on your specific needs and how you prefer to manage your schedule:\n\n- **For comprehensive task and event management with seamless marking features**, **Fantastical** and **BusyCal** are excellent choices.\n- **If you\u2019re already within the Microsoft ecosystem**, **Outlook** offers robust integration with task management tools to help you cross off events efficiently.\n- **For those who prefer a unified approach to tasks and calendar events**, **TickTick** provides a versatile platform to manage and complete your daily activities.\n\nBy selecting one of these apps, you can enhance your daily productivity by effectively managing and marking off your events as you go through your day.",
